        let chem28 = ChemicalsListItem(text: "Dichloroethene", photo: photo28, descrip: "1,1-Dichloroethene is an industrial chemical that is not found naturally in the environment. It is also called vinylidene chloride. 1,1-Dichloroethene is used to make certain plastics, such as flexible films like food wrap, and in packaging materials. It is also used to make flame retardant coatings for fiber and carpet backings, and in piping, coating for steel pipes, and in adhesive applications. Air near factories that make or use 1,1-dichloroethene and air near hazardous waste sites may contain low levels of it. The main effect from breathing high levels of 1,1-dichloroethene is on the central nervous system. Some people lost their breath and fainted after breathing high levels of the chemical. Breathing lower levels of 1,1-dichloroethene in air for a long time may damage your nervous system, liver, and lungs. Studies on workers who breathed 1,1-dichloroethene have not shown an increase in cancer. These studies, however, are not conclusive because of the small numbers of workers and the short time studied. The Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) has determined that 1,1-dichloroethene is a possible human carcinogen.")

