        let photo31 = UIImage(named: "endosulfan.png")!
        let chem31 = ChemicalsListItem(text: "Endosulfan", photo: photo31, descrip: "Endosulfan is a restricted-use pesticide. It is particularly effective against aphids, fruit worms, beetles, leafhoppers, moth larvae, and white flies on a wide variety of crops. Endosulfan is applied to crops by aerial or ground-level foliar spray. The use of endosulfan is being restricted to certain crops and is scheduled to be canceled for all uses by 2016. Touching contaminated soil or fruits or plants that have been sprayed with endosulfan will result in a small amount entering the body through the skin. The main target of endosulfan toxicity is the nervous system. Exposure to high amounts of endosulfan induces hyperactivity and convulsions, regardless of the route of exposure. Severe poisoning may result in death. Studies of occupational and environmental exposure of humans have not provided conclusive evidence that endosulfan can cause cancer. Endosulfan did not cause cancer in animal studies. The Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS), the International Agency for Research on Cancer (IARC), and the EPA have not classified endosulfan as to its ability to cause cancer.")

